info.author: Martin
info.description: # Jocular Jocular is a tool for **Electronically-Assisted Visual Astronomy**. Jocular supports the observation of astronomical objects in near real-time by connecting up a camera to a telescope or suitable lens. It also supports session-planning through extensive deep sky object (DSO) databases, helps to manage your captures, and enables the reloading of previously-captured images. Jocular is documented on Read the Docs.
info.name: jocular
info.summary: A tool for near-live observation of astronomical objects
